      "The most effective techniques for remembering new vocabulary are: the keyword method (linking a new word to a familiar sound or image), spaced repetition (reviewing at growing intervals), active recall (testing yourself rather than re-reading), word association (connecting new words to known words), and using new words in sentences or conversation immediately after learning them. Passive re-reading is the least effective method.",
