        body: "Re-reading a word definition feels productive but creates an illusion of knowing. When you look at a familiar word on a page, your brain recognises it but that is not the same as being able to recall it independently.\n\nRetrieval practice — the act of pulling a word from memory without looking at it — is far more effective. Every time you successfully recall a word, the memory trace strengthens.",
